<div class="wrap">
    <h1>Conceptual Collaboration Model (Original): Local Git + Remote Repository</h1>

    <div class="grid">
      <!-- Developer A -->
      <section class="dev">
        <h2>DEVELOPER A (Local Git)</h2>
        <div class="stack">
          <div class="area">
            <b>Working Directory</b>
            <p>Edit files and run checks locally.</p>
            <div class="pillrow">
              <span class="pill warn">git status</span>
              <span class="pill warn">git diff</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="area">
            <b>Staging Area</b>
            <p>Select changes to include in the next snapshot.</p>
            <div class="pillrow">
              <span class="pill ok">git add</span>
              <span class="pill warn">git restore --staged</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="area">
            <b>Local Repository</b>
            <p>Commit history stored on the developer’s machine.</p>
            <div class="pillrow">
              <span class="pill ok">git commit</span>
              <span class="pill warn">git log</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flows">
          <div class="flow"><b>Push:</b> publish local commits to the remote repository using <code>git push</code>.</div>
          <div class="flow"><b>Fetch:</b> retrieve updates from remote without merging using <code>git fetch</code>.</div>
          <div class="flow"><b>Pull:</b> retrieve and integrate remote updates using <code>git pull</code>.</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Center: Remote -->
      <div class="centercol">
        <section class="remote">
          <div class="title">REMOTE REPOSITORY</div>
          <p class="sub">Shared repository hosted on GitHub (or another Git server). Enables collaboration by exchanging commits.</p>
          <div class="pillrow" style="justify-content:center;margin-top:10px">
            <span class="pill ok">git clone</span>
            <span class="pill warn">git fetch</span>
            <span class="pill ok">git push</span>
            <span class="pill warn">git pull</span>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="legend">
          <h3>Notes</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><code>git clone</code> creates a full local copy of the remote repository.</li>
            <li><code>git push</code> sends committed snapshots to the remote.</li>
            <li><code>git fetch</code> downloads remote changes but does not merge them.</li>
            <li><code>git pull</code> fetches and integrates updates into the current branch.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Developer B -->
      <section class="dev">
        <h2>DEVELOPER B (Local Git)</h2>
        <div class="stack">
          <div class="area">
            <b>Working Directory</b>
            <p>Edit files independently and test locally.</p>
            <div class="pillrow">
              <span class="pill warn">git status</span>
              <span class="pill warn">git diff</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="area">
            <b>Staging Area</b>
            <p>Stage only the changes that are ready to record.</p>
            <div class="pillrow">
              <span class="pill ok">git add</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="area">
            <b>Local Repository</b>
            <p>Commit locally; history is always available offline.</p>
            <div class="pillrow">
              <span class="pill ok">git commit</span>
              <span class="pill warn">git log</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flows">
          <div class="flow"><b>Clone:</b> start by copying the remote with <code>git clone</code>.</div>
          <div class="flow"><b>Pull:</b> stay up to date with <code>git pull</code> before pushing your work.</div>
          <div class="flow"><b>Push:</b> share completed commits using <code>git push</code>.</div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>

    <p style="margin:14px 0 0;color:var(--muted);font-size:12px;line-height:1.45">
      This figure is an original conceptual diagram describing Git’s distributed model: each developer has a full local repository,
      and collaboration occurs by synchronizing commits with an optional remote repository.
    </p>
  </div>

